here are some pitfalls ive learned of working with chatgpt and cursor agents in 2026:
1. agents are too optimistic and positive, sometimes misunderstsnd intent
2. cursor had 99% accuracy when i issued jira-ticket like commands with clear and unambiguous language as well as defined the interface/api layer (asking agents to reverse engineer or guess at comfyui workflows or embedding extra beast2 json in png/web only about 50% successful, complex poorly docd apis).
3. the 1% cursor failure seemed like a small easy fix and it failed repeatedly which made it feel a lot worse
4. chatgpt can lose all context and need full reinitialization if stream gets too incoherent. possibly other failure modes, uncertain at this time.
5. early on designing the beast chatgpt woukd often loop on a few topics, believe it even recommending to create a doc that had already been made with same title in one case (have not confirmed by log check)
6. chatgpt and cursor both can be overconfident and wrong.
7. other than when i explicitly mention it i read every word and punctuation mark of chatgpt replies, i dont skim. speaking of which there was some text id="" cruft but its mixed because it adds some syntax highlighting at the cost of slightly uglier.

